 <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">Effective potentials of Hofmeister salts in aqueous solution</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">IOP</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">The effective pair interaction potentials of monovalent halide anions and alkali cations in bulk solution of a molecular solvent model were determined using atomistic simulations. These properties result from the microstructure of the ionic liquid which is the main ingredient in the hypernetted chain approach of liquid theory. We used an optimized set of Lennard-Jones parameters that are thermodynamically reliable for bulk phases of the Hofmeister salts.</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">IOP</subfield>
 </datafield>
